description: From Latin Sīrēdones, alternative form of Sīrēnes (“the Sirens”) from Ancient Greek Σειρηδώνες (Seirēdṓnes) plural of Σειρηδών (Seirēdṓn) alternative form of Σειρήν (Seirḗn, “Siren”).

entries.meaning: (zoology, obsolete) A larval or neotenic salamander (e.g. the axolotl, Ambystoma mexicanum).
